  "name": "Tormenting Visions",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/affliction_11.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Horror Adventures pg. 140</em></p><p><strong>Type</strong> curse; <strong>Save</strong> Will DC 15</p><p><strong>Effect</strong> The target is haunted by horrible phantasmal visions that distract him at critical moments. He takes a -4 penalty on concentration checks and on saving throws against effects that would impose any of the following conditions on him: confused, dazed, nauseated, shaken, sickened, or stunned. Once per day, when alone or confronted by something novel and strange, he must succeed at a Will save or take 1d3 points of Wisdom damage (or 1d6 points of sanity damage if using the sanity system).</p><p><strong>Cure</strong> The tormenting visions curse can be removed only by <em>remove curse</em> followed by <em>banishment</em>, each cast within 1 minute of each another.</p>",
